fstests-utils release-on-drain <backend-down-cmd> <out-file>

Read wq-ssh JSONL on stdin, write it through to <out-file>, and fire
"<backend-down-cmd> <worker>" in the background whenever a
worker_stopped event with reason in {drained, quarantined} appears.

Both reasons mean the worker has exited its run loop -- "drained"
because the queue emptied, "quarantined" because DEAD_THRESHOLD
consecutive transport errors marked it terminally lost.  Either
way the ssh ControlMaster is gone and the droplet is safe to
destroy.
